biogHists.text:
KUER is a public radio station serving the Salt Lake Valley since 1960, and the State of Utah since 1983.

From the description of The KUER radio records. 2000-2002. (University of Utah). WorldCat record id: 71693320

                  <unitdate>1959</unitdate>
                  <origination>
                     <corpname>University of Utah. Media Services</corpname>
                  </origination>
                  <physdesc>
                     <extent>1 folder</extent>
                  </physdesc>
                  <abstract>KUER was begun as a student-operated radio station under the supervision of Radio and Television Services.  It is now fully professional  and a member of National Public Radio and American Public Radio.  In 1976, a new organization, Media Services, was formed to consolidate all media activities including KUER Radio, KUED Television, and the offices of Instructional Television, Educational Media, and Correspondence Study.  This collection contains an application with associated exhibits made to the Federal Communications Commission for a license to begin operation of KUER Radio.</abstract>
                  <langmaterial>
                     <language>English</language>
                  </langmaterial>
               </did>
            </objectXMLWrap>

                  <abstract>Media Services was created in 1976 and included KUED, KUER, Instructional Television, Educational Media, and Correspondence Study.  Rex L. Campbell served as Director of Radio and Television Services from 1964 to 1975.  Robert M. Reed was General Manager of KUED from 1977 to 1978.  Bruce L. Christensen became General Manager of KUED in 1979 and Director of Media Services in 1981.  This collection contains correspondence, meeting minutes, and subject files primarily from KUED and secondarily from other divisions of Media Services.</abstract>
                  <langmaterial>
                     <language>English</language>
                  </langmaterial>
               </did>
            </objectXMLWrap>
